{"name":"Discern Noise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To hearken at a door and detect the faintest of noises on the other side, perceive the distant footfalls of a wandering monster, or distinguish a single voice in a crowd. Six rounds (one minute) of concentrated listening are required.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Monks practice a few thievish skills. These abilities progress as the monk advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">[</span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> -- see </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Player's Manual</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, p.37]</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253207156,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0Z6NzOE7wzNKfkrn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Longevity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 11th level, ageing process slows. For every 13 years (1 Hyperborean cycle), the monk effectively ages but 1 year.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk 11","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iPWkkv7WnyUR7Nbk"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"33UdImME41JGOUXF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Cellular Adjustment","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Once per day, supernaturally alter cells to heal physical damage equal to 2 hp per level of experience. Alternatively, the monk may confer this healing onto an injured ally. Also, once per week the monk can purge him- or herself or another of disease or poison, per the spells <em>cure disease</em> or <em>neutralize poison</em>, though not lycanthropy.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106879,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"3bB4u0FodwDU4hMs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Superior Willpower","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+2 bonus to saving throws versus any sorcery that would influence the mind, including illusions, charms, etc. This bonus is cumulative with <em>willpower adjustment</em>, if applicable (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>wisdom</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106927,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"AKO6NS6SzvmKkclG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Speak With Nature","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 4th level, <em>speak with animals</em> (as the spell) once per day; at 8th level, also <em>speak with plants</em> (as the spell) once per day.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk 4","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106927,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"DmKaYsXJv0bByrI9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Simulate Death","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 5th level of experience, enter a deep trance in which the monk can feign a deathlike condition, as per the <em>cataleptic state</em> spell (q.v.).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk 5","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106927,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"KjD0PT3uxkDKgXDL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Block Missile","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Deflect a fired arrow, bolt, or bullet; likewise, a hurled axe, boomerang, dagger, dart, javelin, spear, or like weapon. Even spells such as <em>flaming missile</em>, <em>magic ice dart</em>, <em>magic missile</em> or <em>acid arrow</em> can be blocked. Siege missiles, giant-hurled boulders, and the like do not apply. To repel a missile, the monk must make an <em>avoidance</em> saving throw. The monk must drop anything held to use this ability, which can be attempted as many times per round as the monk has levels of experience.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106879,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"OTJ1j7E37GUuR8nP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Empty Hand","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Master of the unarmed attack (hand, foot, knee, elbow, etc.). The monk enjoys the following benefits when fighting sans weapons:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2/1 attack rate; requires two free hands, attacks not exclusively by hand.</li>\n<li>Weapon-like damage (see <strong>Table 44</strong>). The monk may use <em>c&aelig;stuses</em> (leather thongs wrapped around the hands and weighted with iron or lead plates or spikes) for a +1 damage bonus.</li>\n<li>On a natural 20 attack roll, a <em>stunning blow</em> can be delivered. A Small or Medium creature must make a <em>transformation</em> saving throw or be <em>stunned</em> for 2d4 rounds. At 7th level, Large creatures can be stunned, but they are afforded a +4 bonus to the save. Does not affect undead, constructs, oozes, slimes, and the like. If the optional <em>critical hits</em> rule is used (see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>critical hits and misses</em>), the target is stunned in addition to any bonus damage inflicted.</li>\n<li>At 5th level, the <em>empty hand</em> attack (due to heightened <em>ka/qi</em>) is equivalent to a magical weapon; the monk gains a +1 &ldquo;to hit&rdquo; bonus.</li>\n<li>At 12th level, once per day, deliver a <em>quivering palm</em> death blow. The monk mystically vibrates the <em>empty hand</em> to match the rhythm of the target&rsquo;s heart or other vital organ. If hit, the victim must make a <em>death</em> saving throw or die instantly; otherwise, normal damage applies. If the attack misses, subsequent attempts may be made, so long as the monk does nothing else but focus on the <em>quivering palm</em> attacks. <em>Quivering palm</em> has no effect on the undead, constructs, oozes, slimes, and the like.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"R3Rbzs0WGZYZFhbe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Str and Dex","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of strength</em> and <em>dexterity</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>strength</em> and <em>dexterity</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YIplOKcVwiJ20PGF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"VHxXsdjsqDTN8XWU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hide","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To vanish into shadows, camouflage oneself, or flatten one&rsquo;s body to a seemingly impossible degree&mdash;all whilst remaining still as a statue. Only the slightest movement is permissible (e.g., unsheathing a blade, opening a pouch). Hiding is impossible in direct sunlight, or if the monk is observed.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Monks practice a few thievish skills. These abilities progress as the monk advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253228973,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"YmH1P6aCQAG3Z5FM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Defensive Ability","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To avoid and deflect blows and damage through physical, mental, and spiritual (ka/qi) mastery. The monk gains an AC bonus that increases as levels of experience are gained (see <strong>Table 44</strong>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106879,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"aUxM39Y5JzwlakS8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Detect Secret Doors","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Find a secret door on a base 3-in-6 chance.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106880,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"bJuf7DKvAyOMiyMj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Run","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move as swiftly as a tiger. If unarmoured, achieve a movement rate of 50; at 7th level, this speed increases to a superhuman MV 60 for short bursts.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106909,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"hzRUlNg0EwFM8Dqg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Controlled Fall","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 81\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To retard descent of precipitous falls. For every level of experience, the monk can fall 10 feet and sustain no damage, so long as a wall or other stable surface is within a five-foot reach throughout the descent. For falls beyond the monk&rsquo;s limit, normal rules are in force starting at the point at which the <em>controlled fall</em> no longer applies; e.g., a 5th-level monk plummets down a 90-foot pit and thus sustains 4d6 hp damage.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106879,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"jRtQxPRFsQk6HlVE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">(however, see <em>controlled fall</em> ability).</span></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Monks practice a few thievish skills. These abilities progress as the monk advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579106879,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"qPVcyUR4OCsMaeAE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-compendium/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move with preternatural quiet, even across squeaky floorboards, dry leaves, loose debris, and the like. This skill is executed at half the monk's normal movement rate.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 82\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Monks practice a few thievish skills. These abilities progress as the monk advances in levels of experience, comparable to the thief.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">[</span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> -- see </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Player's Manual</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, p.37]</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"monk","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253287286,"modifiedTime":1681579106903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"uzHGdCAvDZiVKAx1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
